DTEND:20260309T000300Z
SUMMARY:UNICO Annual Fish Fry
LOCATION:1101 W. Sligh Avenue Tampa\, FL Tampa \, FL 33604 United States
DESCRIPTION:Mission Statement The United Civic Organization of Tampa\, Fla
 .\, (UNICOs) Mission is to support academic achievement through scholarshi
 ps for students who otherwise could not afford post-secondary education. M
 embers celebrate cultural heritage and fellowship. Our Story UNICO is cele
 brating its 75th Anniversary! Since 1951 UNICO has been a cornerstone of c
 ommunity empowerment\, cultural appreciation\, and educational advancement
  in the Tampa Bay area. Founded by passionate volunteers from Tampas vibra
 nt Cuban\, Sicilian\, and Spanish communitiesincluding business leaders\, 
 skilled tradespeople\, and professionalsUNICO was born with a goal to cele
 brate Latin heritage and inspire the next generation.  What began as stude
 nt achievement awards for excellence in language and the arts has grown in
 to a robust scholarship program\, changing lives and fostering opportuniti
 es. Today\, UNICO proudly provides scholarships to students attending Hill
 sborough College\, the University of South Florida\, and the University of
  Tampa. To date\, over 300\,000 in scholarships has been awarded\, helping
  countless students pursue their dreams. These scholarships\, administered
  by the schools\, focus primarily on supporting students with financial ne
 ed. In 2025 UNICO endowed a Workforce Development Scholarship for trades a
 nd technical careers at Hillsborough College.  Our efforts are fueled by t
 he community we serve. Each year\, UNICO hosts signature fundraising event
 s. On March 8 UNICO will hold its Annual Fish Fry at Lowry Park and open t
 o the public\, celebrating camaraderie and shared purpose. See Annual Even
 ts and Tickets tab for more information. UNICOs much-anticipated Jaibada D
 inner\, an authentic Tampa crab enchilado feast\, and lively Bocce Tournam
 ent\, will take a sabbatical this year. We also welcome support from gener
 ous sponsors and donors who share our vision of creating a brighter future
  through education and community engagement. See Sponsor on web site tab f
 or more information.  At UNICO\, we believe that by honoring our cultural 
 roots and lifting up those in need\, we create a lasting impact for genera
 tions to come. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/186216
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/186216
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:113b4210-a881-49fa-b42a-a183ad882b2e
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260308T140000Z
DTEND:20260308T170000Z
SUMMARY:Ceramics Continued Study
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Ceramics Continued Study is a space for students to enhance th
 eir learning experience with instructor assistance and guiding knowledge. 
 Sign up for a single class to continue working and add the finishing touch
 es on projects youve started in one of our other classes. Sign up for mult
 iple classes to choose your own adventure in hand-building or wheel thrown
  ceramics. Work with your instructor to plan out your projects and make th
 em a reality. Some experience with clay is recommended. 16 Firing costs\, 
 essential tools\, and glazes included. Clay is available for purchase sepa
 rately in studio. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/177516
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/177516
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bfb1cb5b-c1dd-4ec6-a0bb-9be63a8d9953
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260309T140000Z
DTEND:20260309T200000Z
SUMMARY:Workshop: Encaustic Monotype Basics
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:In this specialized class students will learn the process of e
 ncaustic monotype printing and manipulation to those prints using a heated
  hot box. Monotype with a hot box involves creating an encaustic print on 
 a heated hot box which was invented by Paula Roland. The artist applies an
 d manipulates molten wax on the heated surface with tools\, then transfers
  the image to paper. This can be a one-of-kind print or can have layers ad
 ded to create ghost prints. Basic encaustic experience required. Ages 18 \
 n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/177276
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/177276
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ddfe4c1e-40d8-4ec2-9811-52be6c312399
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260310T233000Z
DTEND:20260311T004500Z
SUMMARY:Affordable Energy Community Discussion
LOCATION:2607 E Dr Martin Luther King Jr Blvd Tampa \, FL 33610 United Sta
 tes
DESCRIPTION:Floridians have been hit hard by skyrocketing electricity bill
 s\, but our elected officials can do something about it! Join the Hillsbor
 ough Affordable Energy Coalition (HAEC) for a community discussion about r
 ising energy bills and how we can address this widely and deeply felt prob
 lem. Youll have the opportunity to share your personal story\, speak with 
 experts in the field and local elected officials\, and come together to mo
 ve on affordable energy solutions. Light refreshments and pizza will be se
 rved! \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185751
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185751
END:VEVENT
