SUMMARY:West River BUILD Pre-Construction Public Information Meeting
LOCATION:1006 W. Cypress Street Tampa \, FL 33606 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Pre-Construction Public Information Meeting As c
 onstruction continues on various segments of the West River BUILD Project\
 , join us from 6-8 PM at Beulah Baptist Institutional Church on Wednesday\
 , March 18th for a pre-construction meeting for Segment 5: Columbus Drive 
 from Rome Avenue to North Boulevard. Meet the project team\, ask questions
 \, and learn about whats ahead for this project segment. The West River BU
 ILD (aka West Riverwalk project) is a transformative project that includes
  about 5 miles of roadway upgrades and two miles of new riverwalk along th
 e west side of the Hillsborough River. Itll create new connections\, safer
  roadways\, and super-charge economic opportunities! West Tampa families w
 ill also have more access to the waterfront they can enjoy for generations
 . Full project completion is expected: Spring 2027 To learn more\, visit: 
 westriverbuild.com (https:westriverbuild.com) \n\nPermalink: https://www.t
 ampa.gov/node/186991
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/186991
