SUMMARY:Poetry in the Galleries: TMA x UTampa NEON
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening of live poetry inside the galleries of 
 the Tampa Museum of Art. Inspired by the monumental sculptures and paintin
 gs in Jun Kaneko: Silence Before Sound\, students from the University of T
 ampa will share original poems written in response to the works on view. E
 xperience the exhibition through fresh voices and new perspectives as each
  poet performs beside the artwork that sparked their writing. This special
  collaboration with NEON\, UTampas student-run literary and arts magazine 
 brings together visual art and spoken word. Neon is a student-run literary
  and arts magazine located at the University of Tampa. Lectures are offere
 d free with the cost of daily admission: Thursday evenings are donation ba
 sed\, pay as you will admission \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/
 186881
