SUMMARY:Figure Drawing Study
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Work in your drawing and painting media of choice or explore n
 ew ones. In these three-hour instructor-guided single-session classes\, st
 udents will learn the fundamentals and expand their 2D knowledge while cre
 ating images from life. Learn the basics and grow your techniques with tai
 lored instruction and live model sessions. Ages 18 Drawing materials provi
 ded. These classes do have live Nude Models. \n\nPermalink: https://www.ta
 mpa.gov/node/177266
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/177266
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10fade15-be0e-456b-bd55-334c05bddb03
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260423T190000Z
DTEND:20260423T220000Z
SUMMARY:The Wonderment Weekend
LOCATION:211 South Howard Ave Tampa \, FL 33606 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a celebration of art and whimsy Are you a curious 
 creative? Do you dare to play? Would making more time just for you bring y
 ou more joy? Join us for a whimsical journey to open your heart and mind. 
 Explore with abandon as we engage the artist within through discover\, pra
 ctice and creativity. With each class youll play with new mediums\, work t
 hrough a variety of projects\, and connect with others on their wonderment
  journey. Imagine awe-filled days in an enchanted bungalow with other crea
 tive souls. A leisurely pace of inspiring experiences\, sharing\, making a
 nd lots of play. Creativity helps us break free from modern living and pro
 vides a fresh perspective for renewed vitality. This weekend is an opportu
 nity to make time to love yourself\, radical acceptance through embracing 
 joy. We shall summon our secret strengths\, our creative genius\, and live
  boldy from the heart. April 23 - 25\, 2026 Thursday April 23rd - Welcome 
 Reception  Registration Friday April 24th  Day 1 workshops and evening fre
 e play Saturday April 25th - Day 2 workshops and evening free play Youll s
 pend each day at The Paper Seahorse\, with breaks for lunch and dinner. Th
 is two-day retreat features three immersive workshops (all supplies includ
 ed)\, swag bag\, make-and-takes\, catered lunches\, snacks and light refre
 shments throughout the day\, and extra time for free play! In addition to 
 wonderful workshops\, there will be plenty of time for meditating\, knitti
 ngcrochet\, sketching or to simply be. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.go
 v/node/178896
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178896
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:035b8698-255a-4314-a024-aae6da9d5927
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260423T223000Z
DTEND:20260424T023000Z
SUMMARY:A Legacy of Love: 70 Years of Heart and Hope
LOCATION:402 W Laurel Street Tampa \, FL 33607 United States
DESCRIPTION:Heart of Adoptions Alliance Inc. (HOAA) is a non-profit 501(c)
 (3) licensed child-placing agency dedicated to connecting children with sa
 fe and loving families. HOAAs annual gala fundraiser\, taking place on Thu
 rsday\, April 23\, 2026\, at 6:30 PM at the scenic Bob Buckhorn Tampa Rive
 r Center. This year will be a very special event as we pay tribute to Jean
 ne Tate\, the agencys founder and nationally recognized adoption attorney.
  The event promises an inspiring evening dedicated to supporting vital ado
 ption services. Proceeds will help recruit families for children in foster
  care\, provide post-placement services for birth mothers\, and offer ongo
 ing adoption support to children and their families. \n\nPermalink: https:
 //www.tampa.gov/node/187451
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187451
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2e027161-63fe-4f0b-bc60-2abb68255cef
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260326T001019Z
DTSTART:20260423T220000Z
DTEND:20260424T010000Z
SUMMARY:Remix: The Etruscans
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa FL Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Remix is a series of make-and-take art workshops for adults in
 spired by the Museums current exhibitions with a new project every month. 
 This months project will be inspired by our The Etruscans: A Mysterious It
 alian People (https:tampamuseum.orgthe-etruscans-a-mysterious-italian-peop
 le) exhibition. Paint and decorate your own personal box\, similar to the 
 detailed ash boxes of the Etruscans! Ages 18 Workshops are designed to be 
 enjoyed by participants of any skill level\, and all materials are provide
 d. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/177226
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/177226
END:VEVENT
